	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories  A 48-year-old man is in a critical condition in hospital
after he was shot in Salt River earlier today. Police say the incident took place in Junction Road at about
11:00. Spokesperson, Sgt Hilton Malila, says police were called to
the scene and on arrival found a capsized gold BMW. The car had collided with
other vehicles. “After further investigation, police noticed that there was
a male and a female in the car. A preliminary investigation revealed that the
male person, who was driving the car, sustained multiple gunshot wounds,” says
Malila. The injured man was rushed to hospital in a critical
condition. The passenger sustained no injuries in the incident. The motive for the shooting is under investigation and
police have opened a case of attempted murder. Anyone who witnessed the incident or has any information is
asked to call the Warrant Officer Warren Smith on 021-4862824 or Crime stop on
080010111. No arrests have been made.  24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  